	ITEM 8.01






	Other Events







	 




	On May 2, 2017 Canadian Pacific Railway Limited (the “Company”) announced that the Company has joined K+S Potash Canada (KSPC) in celebrating the grand opening of the Legacy Port mine site. The mine is the first of its kind built in Saskatchewan in more than 40 years, and the rail infrastructure built to serve the mine is the most significant engineering project undertaken by the Company since the mid– 1980s.









	A copy of the news release




	is attached as Exhibit 99.1 to this current report on Form 8- K.











	  








